data.name: richTextBox7.Text
data.value:
This section calculates the capacity of the well bore.
You can enter upto 6 drillpipe/ HWDP/ drill- collars configurations.
The required number of pump cycles can also be calculated.
Press the colored buttons to paste values directly from the other modules.

data.name: richTextBox8.Text
data.value:
This section calculates the various ton miles in operations like Drilling, Coring and Casing.
Please note that, T1 is at a lower depth than T2.
Use the generic converter if using S.I. values.
The yellow background inputs resemeble the casing ton miles extra inputs.

data.name: richTextBox6.Text
data.value:
This section calculates the Buoyancy, Hookload, Overpull and Neutral Point.
The yellow inputs are for drill- pipe, and green inputs are for BHA. You can add 2 drillpipes 4 BHA options.
For BHA, use bottom up approach, starting from 3.

data.name: richTextBox24.Text
data.value: This section calculates the various parameters of a deviated well. Copy the H.D. value from the previous tab. To use it, firstly select the appropriate radio button of either J-Profile or S-Profile. Fill out the details and click 'Solve'. The results will show up in a new tab. Please do not browse other tabs - 'J-I, J-II, S-I, S-II, S-III' . It will not be of any functionality unless the values are filled properly.

data.name: richTextBox3.Text
data.value:
This section allows you to find and use the various dimnesions of drill pipe, drill collar, and heavy weight drill pipe.
To use the functions, select the value, by clicking the check box, you know and click 'Go' to get the other values.
The green background values are self suficient hence requires no other values. Select only the green background value to get the rest.
The white background values, require another value for computation of the third value.
Click the color buttons to copy the values so that you can paste it in the other modules.
Drill Pipe/Drill Collars - API std. Heavy Wt. DP - non API values (not for professional use)
